-- Standard Chartered Said to Market 10-Year Dollar Bond
-- B y   T a n y a   A n g e r e r
-- 2012-01-18T01:18:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/standard-chartered-said-to-market-10-year-dollar-bond.html
Standard Chartered Plc (STAN)  is marketing
a U.S. dollar benchmark 10-year subordinated note, according to
a person familiar with the matter.  Barclays Plc, BNP Paribas SA, Credit Suisse Group AG and
 Standard Chartered  are arranging the sale, the person said,
asking not to be identified as the details are private.
Benchmark typically means $500 million in size.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tanya Angerer in Singapore at 
 tangerer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
